longBusinessSummary: Eastern Michigan Financial Corporation operates as the bank holding company for Eastern Michigan Bank that provides retail and commercial banking services in Michigan. The company offers checking and savings accounts, individual retirement accounts, and certificates of deposit. It also provides submitting small business administration (SBA) paycheck protection program loans; automobile and truck loans; RV, motorcycle, snowmobile, jet ski, boat, and ATV loans; unsecured personal loans; student loans; home mortgage loans; home equity lines of credit and home equity term loans; machinery, equipment, and vehicle loans; working capital lines of credit; farm land, construction, livestock, FSA guaranteed, and long term fixed rates loans; Equipment financing and loans; and commercial real estate, construction and land development, and multi-family dwelling loans. In addition, the company offers online, mobile, and telephone banking services; debit and credit cards; gift cards; safe deposit box services; and electronic payment, merchant, remote deposit capture, lockbox, voice response banking, night deposit, notary, and exchange services. It operates through nine branches in the counties of Sanilac, Huron, and St. Clair, Michigan. The company was founded in 1895 and is headquartered in Croswell, Michigan.
